Sleep(): This Method is used to pause the execution of current thread for a specified 
time in Milliseconds. Here, Thread does not lose its ownership of the monitor and 
resume’s it’s execution

Wait(): This method is defined in object class. It tells the calling thread 
(a.k.a Current Thread) to wait until another thread invoke’s the notify() or 
notifyAll() method for this object, The thread waits until it reobtains the 
ownership of the monitor and Resume’s Execution.